thread.title: Cold War II: Spy Agency Sounds Alarm at Foreign-Interference Levels

author: Rob Taylor
title: Cold War II: Spy Agency Sounds Alarm at Foreign-Interference Levels
text:
Espionage and foreign interference are occurring at greater levels now than at the height of the Cold War, a top intelligence official warned Australian lawmakers, as concerns grow among the U.S. and its allies about Chinese and Russian meddling.
Australia’s domestic spy agency released a dossier of examples to lawmakers at a parliamentary intelligence oversight committee Wednesday.
